New York has an incarceration rate of 443 per 100,000 people, Which means it locks up more people then other wealthy democracies do.

**High inmate Rates?**

Are blacks more likely to get incarcerated more then any other race? Lets take a look at what are the rates of inmates in the past 5 years, after using sufficiant data from Kaggle "NY Daily Inmates In Custody " i came across something that was very interesting. The amount of inmates from 2015 to 2019 went up by mountains. Then i started thinking what are the inmates in these jail systems, what are their race, what are their age? We all know younger age comes with less maturity and more toubles. Some Americans would say Police are known for targeting “Young Black” Americans roughly in their mid 20's to early 30s. Is it true? Whose to say right now maybe they are maybe they are not. But we can tell if there is a pattern in the incarceration to the Black Americans in the United States. lets take a look at what was the incarceration rates from 2015 to 2019.

**Age Inmates**

As we can see the rates of New York inmates has went up by a very great margin in 2019, alot of those inmates ages ranged from 25-30 years old. If we examine the age of the inmates a great amount of inmates age ranges from 25 to 30 years of age. and the values for around those ages was around 250 or more "per age"(25-30). So these inmates so young in age are still incarcerated and just wasting time, for what New York why isnt their a system to help these young aged New Yorkers to become better? New York expects a young aged person to be inmated for so long and come out and know what their next move is, When in reality their is no way or it is not easy. Jobs dont hire, Housing wont take you in. Now that leads to re incarceration.

![scatter age.png](data:image/png;base64,)

**Which race has the most inmate rates**

In 2019 the amount of inmates were at a very high amount as we noticed above roughly over 5500 inmates all together just in 2019. Out of that 5,500 over 3,000 were blacks That is more then half the population of inmates in 2019 put together. So question is, Does New York sentence more time to black inmates? Or is the black community being targeted? After viewing this rates of black inmates and population of inmates in 2019 i would say so. If you look at any other race notice how slim it is compared to the black community. If you add up any other race it doesnt even come up to half the population of inmates in NYC.

![year 2019.png](data:image/png;base64,)

**What if..**

What if the New York took more time in trying to help the back/minority community, help inmates go home and stay out of prisons. Their would more then likely be a less inmate rate over the next few years. Their needs to be more activities for the youth to grow up and not get in touble. When inmates get released their also should be next step programs to keep them out. The goal should be for the incarceration rate to drop not to pick up by more then thousands per year. The more bail reform the better the economy the lower the incarceration rates.
